    <body>
        <p>An alternative way to specify this option is to put it into a <span class="Code" >tls()</span> block, together with any other TLS options. This allows you to separate these options and ensure better readability.</p>
        <p>Make sure that you specify TLS options either using their own dedicated option (<span class="Code">ca-dir()</span>, <span class="Code" >ca-file()</span>, <span class="Code">cert-file()</span>, <span class="Code">cipher-suite()</span>, <span class="Code">key-file()</span>, <span class="Code">peer-verify()</span>, and <span class="Code">ssl-version()</span>), or using the <span class="Code">tls()</span> block and inserting the relevant options within <span class="Code">tls()</span>. Avoid mixing the two methods. In case you do specify TLS options in both ways, the one that comes later in the configuration file will take effect.</p>
    </body>
